  Sightseer is a webapp that allows users to log in and plan out their trip the way they want in Vancouver. 
  <br>
  <br>1. Users input their starting location
  <br>
  <br>2. Sightseer displays various attractions sorted into their respective categories
  <br>
  <br>3. Choose between Sightseeing, Restaurants, Bars and Clubs, and much more. 
  <br>
  <br>4. Sightseer will provide attributes such as estimated cost, distance from starting point, and a general description. 
  <br>
  <br>5. Sightseer uses Google Map’s API to offer the most efficient route based upon the user’s mode of travel. 
  <br>
  <br>6. Total estimated cost and estimated time for each trip will be displayed in case the users have such restraints. 
  <br>
  <br>7. Users can then save their trips for later access and have separate trips planned for different days or they can revisit and perform the same trip
